\begin_layout Standard
Welcome to 
\series bold
Starlit Skies
\series default
, a roleplaying game for three to five people – two to four players and
 one person who serves as the game's Host.
 In this game, you play a Starlit, a shining hero born of the end of the
 world - and now fights to sustain what remains and keep alive the one thing
 humanity will always have; their hopes and dreams.
 In other words; a magical girl.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This system is designed to tell stories like those of the magical girl genre,
 and for higher-powered campaigns where combat can be avoided through diplomacy
 or heart-felt appeals – and yet, just as often, cosmic forces conspire
 such that there is no choice but to fight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This book presents a specific setting, but the rules in it can be used for
 most of the magical girl genre with only slight changes.
 You may want to check the Variant Rules section for optional rules that
 may make this system match your setting better.
 For stories in different genres, the archive containing this document contains
 a separate conversion guide that has advice and tips for changing the rules
 of Starlit Skies to suit a broad range of genres.
\end_layout

